      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "How does it looks like one of the biggest open pit from Europe and what are the consequences? Let's hit the road... From the historical center we head to the The Big Lake('Tăul Mare'). Once we get here you still have to climb a little until you meet an asphalted road. Follow this road up, to reach the Copper Open Pit - 'Rosia Poieni'. Here it looks like dessert: dry soil, no vegetables, a shaved mountain and rusty huge machines. Continue with the second part of the trail - the road to 'Geamăna'. So get back on the asphalted road until you meet an unpaved road at the left. Follow this road through 'Muntari', 'Poiana' and 'Vința' villages, until you reach the waste lake 'Geamana'. The 2nd part of the trail is quite long so we recommend to get back at Casa Petri and go to 'Geamana' by car.",
          "moreDetailsLink": "https://www.google.ro/maps/dir/Geam%C4%83na/Casa+Petri,+DC146,+Ro%C8%99ia+Montan%C4%83/@46.3427615,23.063825,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x4749335e58fe877f:0x883a3e3ec5d25d8a!2m2!1d23.2042788!2d46.3299984!1m5!1m1!1s0x474ecce046c99d41:0xc76f83a95070630c!2m2!1d23.13005!2d46.306754!3e0?hl=ro",
